  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Retail Associate/Customer Service Associate",
  "description": "<ul><li>Operate the Point-of-Sale (POS) system efficiently to record, accept, and verify payments (Cash, NETS, Credit Cards, and Digital Wallets).</li><li>Proactively share product knowledge with customers (e.g., origin of food items, cooking tips, or best-sellers).</li><li>Recommend complementary products or current \"Purchase-with-Purchase\" (PWP).</li><li>Introduce new product arrivals or seasonal specials to customers during the checkout process.</li><li>Greet customers warmly, handle inquiries about product availability, and manage basic feedback or returns professionally.</li><li>Stay updated on current store promotions, member loyalty programs, and seasonal discounts to advise customers accurately.</li><li>Assist in replenishing stocks on shelves and ensuring products are displayed according to quality standards.</li><li>Maintain cleanliness and hygiene of the cashier counter and surrounding retail floor.</li><li>Perform cash float verification at the start of shifts and daily cash/credit settlements at the end of the day.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum Secondary School education or equivalent.</li><li>Good with simple math and basic computer use </li><li>Confident in talking to people and good at suggesting items to customers.</li><li>Friendly, helpful, and enjoys interacting with different people every day</li><li>Able to work on a rotating shift schedule, including weekends and Public Holidays.</li></ul>",
